<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uapprenhightowerr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Appren Hightowerr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/02 11:19:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=348.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing the Mage?</span><hr size=1> I mostly solo'ed for exp, although I have been grouping at all levels.<br>
<br>
Here are some of my favourite solo spots. Probably will be some Luclin spots that are better, dunno.<br>
<br>
16-20 Lake Rathe, Aviak Guards.<br>
20-30 South Karana, aviaks and gnolls, LOIO....gah, Everfrost Mammoths.<br>
30-35 Timorous Deep, Golra Island. - Crystal Caves - Thurgadin Mines (lots of chanters around for clarity <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
35-40 OT, EW at Ulthorks, Giants in FM. Solo/farm Sol A.<br>
40-49 OT, Dreadlands (might be a bit hard solo yet), Dwarves in BB (good until 47). Groups in Sol B.<br>
And the big goodie in the end, 49-whatever...but blue until 54, Wizards and Necro NPC in Neriak Third gate.<br>
55plus I have been solo in Thurgadin, Kael, Cobalt Scar, (still in neriak every now and then) , Maiden's eye (chain casting a must) , Scarlet desert.<br>
<br>
<br>
For tactics, in the middle levels pet heal, nuke, heal, nuke can be a good tactic, but from 40 and on the heal is rather pathetic.<br>
<br>
Start practicing chain casting pets in your 40s, after you get 49 pets it starts to be a very viable tactic, and for quite a few solo spots in mid 50s chain casting is THE most efficient way, especially if you are conjure specialized (Im evocation myself) .<br>
